  "event_preview": "The Long Beach Street Circuit is a 1.968-mile (3.167 km) temporary 11-turn street course in downtown Long Beach, California. IMSA's annual California sprint is the fourth round of the 2026 WeatherTech SportsCar Championship season and one of the most unique events on the calendar: because of the narrow confines of the street circuit, competition is limited to just two classes, Grand Touring Prototype (GTP) and GT Daytona (GTD), with 28 cars entered across the two categories. The race runs for 100 minutes with a mandatory driver change required during the event.\n\nPorsche Penske Motorsport arrives looking to remain unbeaten in 2026. The No. 7 Porsche 963 of Felipe Nasr and Julien Andlauer has already won the Rolex 24 At Daytona and the Mobil 1 Twelve Hours of Sebring. Nasr also won at Long Beach in 2025 with Nick Tandy, and the No. 7 took its first global win at this circuit in 2023 with Nick Tandy and Mathieu Jaminet. Among the notable GTP lineup changes for Long Beach, Laurin Heinrich moves from the No. 7 to the No. 5 JDC-Miller MotorSports Porsche 963 alongside Tijmen van der Helm, while Frederik Vesti steps into the No. 31 Cadillac Whelen entry in place of Earl Bamber, who is committed to the FIA WEC 6 Hours of Imola.\n\nIn GTD, AO Racing returns to defend its 2025 class win with Harry King and Mikkel Pedersen in the No. 177 Porsche, while Vasser Sullivan brings back the No. 89 Lexus of Jack Hawksworth and Frankie Montecalvo. The No. 36 DXDT Racing Corvette also marks the return of Robert Wickens in his second IMSA sprint season alongside Mason Filippi.\n\nThe all-time WeatherTech Championship qualifying records at Long Beach are held by Filipe Albuquerque in GTP with a 1:09.909 (101.343 mph), set in April 2023, and by Parker Thompson in GTD with a 1:17.357 (91.585 mph), set in April 2024.",
  "event_preview_ru": "Long Beach Street Circuit — временная 11-поворотная уличная трасса длиной 1,968 мили (3,167 км) в центре Long Beach, California. Ежегодный калifornийский спринт IMSA — четвёртый этап WeatherTech SportsCar Championship 2026 и одно из самых необычных событий календаря: из-за узких границ уличного круга соревнование ограничено двумя классами — Grand Touring Prototype (GTP) и GT Daytona (GTD), на старт выходит 28 машин. Гонка длится 100 минут с обязательной сменой пилота.\n\nPorsche Penske Motorsport приезжает, стремясь остаться непобеждённым в 2026 году. Porsche 963 No. 7 Felipe Nasr и Julien Andlauer уже победил на Rolex 24 At Daytona и Mobil 1 Twelve Hours of Sebring. Nasr также выиграл в Long Beach в 2025 году с Nick Tandy, а No. 7 одержал здесь первую глобальную победу в 2023 году с Nick Tandy и Mathieu Jaminet. Среди заметных изменений составов GTP на Long Beach Laurin Heinrich переходит из No. 7 в Porsche 963 No. 5 JDC-Miller MotorSports вместе с Tijmen van der Helm, а Frederik Vesti занимает место Earl Bamber в Cadillac Whelen No. 31 — Bamber занят на 6 Hours of Imola FIA WEC.\n\nВ GTD AO Racing защищает классовую победу 2025 года с Harry King и Mikkel Pedersen на Porsche No. 177, а Vasser Sullivan возвращает Lexus No. 89 Jack Hawksworth и Frankie Montecalvo. Corvette No. 36 DXDT Racing также отмечает возвращение Robert Wickens во второй спринт-сезон IMSA вместе с Mason Filippi.\n\nАбсолютные квалификационные рекорды WeatherTech Championship в Long Beach: GTP — 1:09.909 (101,343 mph), Filipe Albuquerque, апрель 2023; GTD — 1:17.357 (91,585 mph), Parker Thompson, апрель 2024.",
  "youtube_id": "Ya_b3xz_G-s"
